      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The race has been decimated by scratchings. POISONOUS (1) four-year-old who resumes today after he showed good early speed on debut before fading to run last over 1100m at Randwick Kensington in a Super Maiden last June. Pulled up (4/5) lame in the near hind leg on that occasion. Two good trial wins should have him ready for this. The one to beat. WRITTEN DOLL (3) Written By gelding from a Choisir mare on debut for the Pfieffer yard. Impressed in two good trial wins and should get through the conditions. Shapes as the main danger. SIDE QUEST (6) Sidestep filly from Skein on debut for the Quinton stable. Two latest trials have been okay and has a host of gear going on for her debut. Stays in the mix. ROCKIN' RED (2) three-year-old gelding by Red Henno out of Our Song Rocks on debut for the Jake Hull yard. Finished fourth at Hawkesbury in his latest trial over 800m. Bred to handle the conditions and keep safe.",
